m being of independent interest, such approximate solutions serve as a foolproof basis for testing numerical algorithms. This first volume presents asymptotic methods in oscillation and resonance problems described by ordinary differential equations, whereby the second volume will be devoted to applications of asymptotic methods in waves and boundary value problems. Contents Asymptotic expansions and series Asymptotic methods for solving nonlinear equations Nonlinear oscillator in potential well Autoresonances in nonlinear systems Asymptotics for loss of stability Systems of coupled oscillators  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aKleine Parameter. 4aNichtlineare Gleichungen. 7aMATHEMATICS / Differential Equations / General.2bisacsh  aNonlinear equations.  aapproximate solutions.  aglobal asymptotics.  asmall parameter.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Studies in Nonlinear Analysis and Applicationsz978311064709908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2017z9783110548204oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831103827230 cprintz978311033554540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311033568240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110335682423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110335682/original  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-064709-9  DG Studies in Nonlinear Analysis and Applications  a978-3-11-07